## The Catch (Be Honest)

### **AI can't do everything:**

**AI is great for:**
✅ Boilerplate code
✅ Common patterns
✅ Debugging
✅ Explaining concepts
✅ Converting between frameworks

**AI struggles with:**
❌ Novel, complex logic
❌ App-specific business rules
❌ Optimization (it works, but slowly)
❌ Knowing what you actually want

**You still need to:**
- Understand the code (don't just copy-paste blindly)
- Make product decisions
- Test thoroughly
- Debug edge cases

**But:** AI removes 70% of the grunt work, letting you focus on the creative 30%

